snippet.textDisplay:
Hey guys!
I've sent this message through the "contact us" option on your website,
But I Figure it would be good to write it in here too:


So the last 5 days Ive been working against the clock and really hard on Recording, Filming, Producing, Editing and Mixing a 1 minute song with a video especially for #LivingRoomsGotTalent

I did make a Submission in time because I knew I have to, (was at 6:30AM in my local time after a night with no sleep), But after 5 hours of sleep I watched the video againt and Felt disgraced for the Audio Mix work I've done, Which made it impossible to enjoy the music, all the different Guitar / Bass / Vocal parts.
So today I had one banana and peanutbutter for breakfast as I Re-Mixed it all,
I am now proud to say It sounds good and I do stand behind it!!

So, I kindly ask you to understand my situation, I am really afraid you'd listen to the first video (which I uploaded on YouTube and submitted to your special website), because I know so many details are missed while The better version is already made and Online!!

The link to my Funky Groove: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1USmqop8Tc0

Thank you for your time reading this message, I cross my fingers you will get to this before moving to the finalists stage.
And btw, you guys rock... I'm a subscriber for the last year or so, I really love your content.

Roy Teicher.

snippet.textDisplay:
I am Muhammad from Pakistan currently living in dubai for last 9 years,
I’ve gone through some of the toughest times in n my life for las 3 years
Lost a lot of money in a scam
Last year my Daughter got brain haemorrhage which caused her heart strokes. With the grace of GOD she survived but it caused me a big debt due to the hospital bills.
I spent whatever i had to pay the bills around 20K $ with help of my colleagues and friends, then i hd to pay for the VISA for her I didn’t have anything but the hope for some salaries to come. It got so late i beard a lot of over stay fine to get my daughter legal here, again which i did from my credit card.
January 27, 2020 i lost my mother back my home land for which i had to take my family for the funeral. But I couldn’t afford to bring my family back with me here in n Dubai due to the financial burden i had.
The company where i am employed is in a real bad time due to the financial crises which caused me around 9 months of salaries unpaid so far, just getting some amount to survive which couldn’t even pay my rent and i lived a long time with the credit cards. This is the time where I’ve nothing to pay my rent for last 3 months, credit card bills or to send money to my family back home.
I’ve 3 and a half yer old lovely boy whom i named in the love of Prophet Jesus (PBUH) as EISA , and my 9 month old daughter, i told the story about. And again with the grace of GOD i am blessed with a new hope of my 3rd baby which is expected to come in this world by the end of July 2020.
All these things put me in such a crucial time that due to the COVID-19 and financial crisis in the market i am unable to sleep and the calls from the banks that threatening for legal action against me,
I have no words further
Need a help.......

Love this idea. Unfortunately I'm not in quarantine because I'm in the front lines and I'm fighting for the lives of the covid patients, my family, and mine.

I know Yes Theory is all about reaching out and helping the community so this would be the perfect time to raise awareness about the lack of personal protective equipment for hospitals all across the nation. I'm from San Diego, CA and the hospital I work at is short on gloves, N95/surgical masks, disinfectants, etc. Management mentioned using bandanas in place of masks.. It's a complete joke. Myself and the other nurses who are taking care of these covid patients are risking our own lives because we do not have enough resources and proper equipment. If this continues, the nurses, doctors, and medical staff will slowly become defeated. If anyone can bring attention to this issue at hand, Yes Theory are the ones to do it during this uncertain time. #getmeppe
